$interpreted: Ru-yi: *heavy breathing*...whew...Rune, you're too heavy...I'm about to collapse...
Hutchinson: ...Finally, we found a way out...lucky for us, we've escaped with our lives.
Hanbei: Not all of us.
Sophie: I haven't heard anything since then...I hope Sanchez is okay.
Maria: War-War-Warning! Living organism is approaching!
Sophie: Maybe Sanchez got away...!?
Rune: ——Sanchez!
Ru-yi: It's......him again. Why won't he just die?
Lazer: Good question, my mammalian friend. I've asked myself that question many times.
Lazer: The faithful here in the Desert might say that the Serpent God is not ready to release me.
Hanbei: But you don't believe that, do you? After all, you're not a lizard.
Lazer: Didn't you hear what the High Priest said? I'm not human and I'm not lizard. I am......a chameleon.
Rune: Sanchez!? What did you do to him!?
Lazer: I have no idea what happened to him. I left him back there. He's probably drowned in his own blood by now.
Lazer: That worthless piece of excrement doesn't deserve to have his corpse handled properly.
Rune: ——Don't say that about SANCHEZ!!
Sophie: *groan*...I don't feel so good...
Ru-yi: I feel...dizzy...
Hanbei: I'm gonna throw up...
Lazer: Your wounds...are very interesting.
Sophie: *groan*...dizzy...
Rune: He's gone...!
Sophie: Rune——Eh!
Clark: ...All my power's been sucked dry, is this...?
Lazer: ...Walk eastward for about a day's time. That will place you outside the Desert Kingdom. You'll soon reach the Desert Bazaar.
Sophie: What's your point, you monster!?
Lazer: I'm giving you one last chance. Don't return to the Desert Kingdom. Stop snooping around. Otherwise...
Sophie: ...Wait!
Lazer: You are lucky just to be alive. All of this has nothing to do with peasants like you. Leave.
Sophie: ...But why? Why don't you just kill us? You mentioned the Queen. Did the High Priest threaten you?
Lazer: ......
Believer: Master, the laboratory has been wiped clean.
Devious: Let's see...good, good...no damage. Demihumans from the Feather Clan are valuable research subjects. He must not be injured. Hssssss.
Believer: Devious, if this boy is indeed a member of the Feather Clan, don't you think we should notify the sect?
Devious: No.
Believer: But our relationship with the Feather Clan...
Devious: If the sect learns of this, they'll learn of my true plans.
Devious: I've wanted to work on such a research subject for some time now. The most valuable research material has been saved for the final experiment.
Lazer: I've returned.
Devious: Ah, General Lazer! Welcome back! Where did the cockroaches run off to?
Lazer: Must you ask? Or do you think I don't take the Queen's matters seriously?
Lazer: You'll never see them in the Desert Kingdom ever again.
Devious: Hsssss...well done. Truly worthy of being called a general. There's no better feeling than exterminating pests~
Lazer: And what of the human I brought back? Have you killed him?
Devious: I've injected him with a paralyzing agent.
Devious: Let's let the worm live for a while. Who knows? Perhaps he will be of use in the future...
Lazer: ...As long as you're satisfied.
Devious: However, you're not one to show mercy. Why did you spare him?
Lazer: ...I've acted rashly before. I don't make the same mistake twice. Is that all? I ought to return to the Queen.
Devious: Anxious to return to your queen? You truly are a loyal servant.
Devious: I hope that the general remains this loyal. Hssssss.
Lazer: ...Thank you for the reminder, High Priest.
Devious: Oh, it's mutual my friend. If you didn't care whether she lived or died, then I wouldn't be able to threaten you with her little secret.
Devious: Who would have thought that the current queen......isn't actually the queen?
Devious: You've played me long enough...
Lazer: If you dare speak of this——
Devious: The queen of the people will be given a pauper's funeral...hssss....
Devious: General Lazer, don't forget that the one who should be scared is you, not me.
Lazer: ......
Sophie: Clark! How's Rune?
Clark: I'm trying my best, but Rune's injuries are too serious...it looks like he won't be able to regain consciousness for the time being.
Sophie: ...oh...
Clark: I'm sorry. I knew I should have spent more time studying healing Runes.
Sophie: Don't say that, Clark. You're injured as well. I'm the one who is unable to help...
Maria: Cl-Cl-Cl-Clark. Chu-Chu-Chu-Chu isn't moving!
Clark: Ah, both of us were thrown into the air...
Clark: Luckily...it was only some of Chu Chu's parts that were broken. Once I find the parts I'll be able to fix it up in no time.
Maria: Won-Won-Won-Won-Wonderful, Chu Chu! Maria will-Maria will-Maria will take extra care of you in the future!
Clark: You should worry about yourself, Maria. Your system crash seems to be rather serious...
Sophie: *sigh*...
Clark: Sophie, I don't want you to worry about all this. I'll do my best...Rune is going to be fine.
Sophie: Clark, you're such a reliable person. But me...I'm useless...
Sophie: What's more, I told everyone to have hope and yet I couldn't do a single thing. And Elio...
Clark: ...I wouldn't say that you didn't do anything.
Sophie: Huh?
Clark: ——We must go to the Rune Academy to ask for help.
Clark: Maria and I are currently unable to go and Rune must rest. It looks like we're going to need to rely on you and the troupe.
Sophie: You mean the Academy in the Valley? Past the Kingdom of the Sun?
Clark: Yes. I know the route is long and dangerous...
Clark: Now that I think of it, both Rune and Elio came into your life as a result of pure fate. It's too much to ask you to risk your life...
Clark: Forget it, just act like I never said any——
Sophie: Forget it!?
Sophie: I'm not going to forget it! I'm going, and that's that!
